Exercise 1: Investigating the User Experience (UX) of a Real Product and a Digital Product
Objective: To develop critical thinking and creative thinking skills and problem analysis

Choose an everyday product (such as a pen, chair, or anything...) and analyze its user experience.
Choose a website or mobile app and analyze its user experience.

Answer the questions:
•	Is there anything in the design of this product that you find frustrating or difficult to use?
•	What suggestions do you have to improve the user experience of this product?
•	Does your improvement affect the safety of the product?
•	Is your suggestion easy to use?
•	Can the user use it without special training?
•	Does your suggestion affect the aesthetics of the product's design in the user experience?
